<P>If your hou&s;e is &s;uperintended by a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> hou&s;e|keeper, and your &s;ervants are accountable to her, let your hou&s;ekeeper be accountable to your&s;elf, and let her be entirely governed by your direc|tions. Carefully examine her <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, and &s;uffer no extravagancies or unne&s;&s;ary articles to pa&s;s unnoticed. Let the&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> brought to you every morning; what they contain will then be ea&s;ily recollected without <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> your me|mory; and your accounts being &s;hort will be ad|ju&s;ted with le&s;s trouble and with more exactne&s;s. Should you at any time have an upper &s;ervant,
