<P>One &s;hould always have &s;ome re&s;ources and la&s;t &s;hifts: calculate your &s;trength and your courage; and for this end, in all ca&s;es where you have any apprehen&s;ions, con&s;ider every thing at the wor&s;t. Wait for the misfortune that may happen to you with firmne&s;s: look it bravely in the face; view
