<P>The fir&s;t duty of civil life is to take care of others; &s;uch as live only for them&s;elves fall into contempt, and are neglected by every body. If you are for requiring too much from others, they will refu&s;e you every thing, their friend&s;hip, their affections, and their &s;ervices. Civil life is a mutual intercour&s;e of good offices: the mo&s;t valuable part of mankind go &s;till further: by promoting the
